    If a learner of English could master this small core then, it was assumed, they could understand every entry in the dictionary.
    In LDOCE, the senses for each word type are grouped into homographs: sets of senses with related meanings.
    For example, one of the homographs of bank means Stevenson and Wilks Interaction of Knowledge Sources in WSD bankl n 1 land along the side of a river, lake, etc.
